dc_description_s: Includes 5 insets: A. Tōkyō: density of population. Scale approximately 1:357,142  -- B. Tōkyō: Functional difffrentiation. Scale approximately 1:357,142 -- C. Tōkyō: relief. Scale approximately 1:173,913 -- D. Tōkyō: Bay area. Scale approximately 1:1,176,470 -- [Detail of downtown]. Scale approximately 1:28,571. Map shows Ku (Ward) and Greater Tokyo boundaries; government and private electrified railroads; central urban lines; comercial and industrial buildings; open spaces; public utilities. On verso: "Index of numbers on map proper". Base map: "Map of Greater Tokyo," published by Tokyo Geographical Association, Jan. 15 1936. Reprinted by BMP no 1, GHQ. AFPAC. U.S. Army, August, 1945. "No. 5279.1 - R & A, OSS: 17 October 1944".
dc_publisher_s: [Washington, D.C.] : Office of Strategic Services, Branch of Research and Analysis, 1944.
